The Kilimani Street Festival held on Saturday afternoon saw diverse vendors showcase their products to the Kilimani community. People showed up in large numbers to mark the festival which takes place quarterly.The aim of this event is encourage familiarisation with your neighbour for a safer and friendlier community feeling.Kilimani Project Foundation chairperson Irungu Houghton emphasised on the importance of communication in the community so as to air grievances like security issues, bad roads among others, making the project a voice to the county government to solve these issues.